Two people have been killed in a plane crash near Hartbeespoort Dam, west of Akasia, Pretoria, at around midday on Saturday. ER24 spokesperson Ross Campbell said a Search & Rescue team and the police were already on the scene when ER24 paramedics arrived. "The bodies of two men were found in the wreckage [of the light aircraft] - they showed no signs of life and were declared dead on arrival," he said. It is unclear what caused the accident but Campbell said authorities were on scene to investigate. GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter